    <div class="WordSection3">
      <div>
        <a name="sec_1" id="sec_1"></a>
        <h1>1<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Overview</h1>
        <div><a name="sec_1.1" id="sec_1.1"></a><h2>1.1<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&#xA0; </span>Introduction</h2>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_79a5c641-6720-cfe3-ec4f-52e847c38fa2" id="_79a5c641-6720-cfe3-ec4f-52e847c38fa2"></a>This document has been produced by the IHO Nautical Information Provision Working Group (NIPWG) in response to a requirement to produce a data product that can be used as a Nautical Publication Information Overlay (NPIO) within an Electronic Chart Display and Information System (ECDIS). It is based on the IHO S-100 framework Specification and the ISO 19100 series of standards. It is a vector Product Specification that is primarily intended for encoding the content of Catalogues of Nautical Products, for navigational purposes.</p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_4162cfe4-3f5e-eded-ad6f-8627a7668b02" id="_4162cfe4-3f5e-eded-ad6f-8627a7668b02"></a>Catalogue of Nautical Products (CNP) datasets describe the availability of paper charts, ENCs and other nautical products, applications for navigational purposes, online services and e-Navigation services. This includes their issue date, status, producing agency, and coverage.</p>
</div>
